WHO   — Bomb to Cult Classic — the film's own redemption arc
WHAT  — The film's own second act: proof that a flop can be wrong about itself, and that an audience can overrule a box office.
WHERE — MLR · Mallrats (1995)  Framework inputs: Mallrats (1995, dir. Kevin Smith, Gramercy/View Askew); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Mallrats' real story is its afterlife — the redemption the reviews didn't predict.
HOW   — By failing on release and winning slowly, on tape and disc and quotation, until the verdict flipped.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I bombed, and I was buried, and then everybody quoted me for thirty years. The box office was wrong about me.

